cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper presents a new approach to improve the discriminative ability of deep generative models for both supervised and semi-supervised learning. The paper focuses on the application of deep learning in classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks as the generative and recognition models, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of regularization terms and efficient algorithms, which could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
